==Party Data Structure==

Character data is stored in RAM at fixed offsets:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Address !! Size !! Description
|-
| $60-$6f || 16 bytes || Prince of Midenhall data
|-
| $70-$7f || 16 bytes || Prince of Cannock data
|-
| $80-$8f || 16 bytes || Princess of Moonbrooke data
|}

===Character Data Format===
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $00 || 1 byte || Current HP (low)
|-
| $01 || 1 byte || Current HP (high)
|-
| $02 || 1 byte || Max HP (low)
|-
| $03 || 1 byte || Max HP (high)
|-
| $04 || 1 byte || Current MP
|-
| $05 || 1 byte || Max MP
|-
| $06 || 1 byte || Strength
|-
| $07 || 1 byte || Agility
|-
| $08 || 1 byte || Defense (base)
|-
| $09 || 1 byte || Experience (low)
|-
| $0a || 1 byte || Experience (mid)
|-
| $0b || 1 byte || Experience (high)
|-
| $0c || 1 byte || Level
|-
| $0d || 1 byte || Status flags
|-
| $0e || 1 byte || Weapon equipped
|-
| $0f || 1 byte || Armor equipped
|}

